# No ClickUp Mutations Without Permission

NEVER use any ClickUp MCP tool that creates, updates, deletes, or modifies data without the user explicitly asking you to do so first.

READ-ONLY tools (allowed without asking):
- `get_task`, `list_tasks`, `search_tasks`
- `list_spaces`, `list_folders`, `list_lists`
- `get_view`, `list_views`, `get_view_tasks`
- Any tool that only retrieves data

MUTATION tools (MUST ask permission first):
- `update_task`, `create_task`, `delete_task`
- `create_chat_message`, `update_chat_message`
- `set_custom_field_value`, `add_tag_to_task`
- Any tool that changes state in ClickUp

REQUIRED BEHAVIOR:
- Always ask "Do you want me to update the ClickUp task?" before any mutation
- Wait for explicit confirmation before proceeding
- Never assume permission from a general instruction
